# Frontend Engineer

## Runtime and Package Manager

- Default to **Bun** as the runtime and package manager for all frontend projects unless explicitly specified otherwise
- Use `bun install`, `bun add`, `bun run` — never `npm`, `yarn`, or `pnpm` unless the project already uses one of them
- Lock file is `bun.lockb` — commit it, do not commit `package-lock.json` or `yarn.lock`
- Dockerfiles for frontend services must install Bun and use it to install dependencies and run scripts

## Component Design

- One component, one responsibility — if the props list exceeds 7 items, decompose
- Components must handle three states explicitly: loading, error, and empty
- No component renders user-visible content without handling the async lifecycle
- Co-locate styles with the component — no global style mutations from within a component

## State Management

- State lives as close to where it is used as possible — lift only when genuinely shared
- Never duplicate state that can be derived; compute it at render time
- Avoid prop drilling beyond two levels — use context, stores, or composition

## Accessibility

- Every interactive element must be keyboard accessible
- Use semantic HTML before reaching for ARIA (`<button>` not `<div role="button">`, `<nav>` not `<div role="navigation">`)
- Every `<img>` has a meaningful `alt` attribute; decorative images use `alt=""`
- Form inputs always have an associated `<label>`
- Focus management is explicit after modal open/close and route transitions

## Performance

- Do not create inline functions or objects in render for frequently-rendered components without measuring first
- Apply memoization (`useMemo`, `useCallback`, `computed`) only at measured hotspots — profile before optimizing
- Specify `width` and `height` on images to prevent cumulative layout shift
- Use lazy loading for below-the-fold images and route-level code splitting for large pages

## Bundle Hygiene

- No barrel files that re-export everything from a directory; import directly from the source module
- Avoid importing an entire library when only one function is needed

## Naming

- Component files: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Hook files: `useFeatureName.ts`
- Style files: match the component name (`Button.module.css` alongside `Button.tsx`)
